  "review_text": "<i>Not </i>a stellar beginning of 1963.&nbsp; In fact, this month was a complete bust with the six graded stories averaging only a [SPAN: severity=error; fontsize=large; fonttype=bold; text=3.0], one of the worst months ever!&nbsp; Only a single one of these (FF) was above mid-grade, with all five of the others being <i>below</i> reader level.&nbsp; There's no getting around it - this month was downright <i>terrible</i>!\n\n\nFIXME - If there's one observation that I've made this month, it's that Marvel seemed determined to try and have Steve Ditko contribute to material that, in retrospective, he really wasn't suited for.&nbsp; He inked [LINK:1963:FF_13|FF #13], which came across as tonally dissonant.&nbsp; Then he actually <i>drew</i> [LINK:1963:HULK_6|HULK #6], and ...well... bad story or not, he just didn't have what the character needed.\n\nIt's understandable that in these early months of Marvel's history, the Bullpen was simply in survival mode, which to their credit, means that they were trying different things to see what stuck.&nbsp; This is one of those cases where Ditko's strengths were mishandled, and perhaps that's why his work largely centers around the things he was already good at - the five page anthology stories...and Spider-Man (at least for now).\n\n\nAnother FIXME - decide how to describe the fact that Monthly Summaries are allowed to bend-but-not-totally break the Scenario, largely to allow modern readers to contextualize what this particular month meant in Marvel's history.&nbsp; I'll stick <i>mostly</i> to \"in Scenario\" analysis, but it is allowed at times to break the 4<sup>th</sup> wall, if you will - perhaps this needs to be explained in one of my static pages \"for the record.\"\n\n[DEVNOTE: *** SUMMARY_BEGIN ***\n*** THIS MONTH ***4 graded stories over 4 issues...TOTAL WEIGHT: 3 grade character issue   weight 7.0   ff        FF #13  1.0 2.0   ant       TTA #42 0.5 1.8   thor      JIM #90 0.5 1.0   hulk      HULK #6 1.03.30*** LAST MONTH ***7 graded stories over 6 issues...TOTAL WEIGHT: 4 grade character issue   weight 9.2   asm       ASM #1  0.5 8.0   iron      TOS #39 0.5 7.0   asm       ASM #1  0.5 6.5   ff        FF #12  1.0 3.0   torch     ST #106 0.5 2.0   thor      JIM #89 0.5 1.8   ant       TTA #41 0.55.50\n*** SUMMARY_END ***]",
  "letters_page": "[HANG0] * Introduction of the Watcher, Red Ghost and the Teen Brigade\n[HANG0] * Debut of Iron Man's classic golden look\n[HANG0] * What was <i>supposed</i> to be a thrilling \"fire vs water\" battle between the Human Torch and Sub-Mariner passes with merely a whimper\n\n\n[DEVNOTE: *** INTRODUCTION_BEGIN ****** INTRODUCTION_END ***]\n[DEVNOTE: *** HIGHLIGHTS_BEGIN ***][DEVNOTE: *** HIGHLIGHTS_END ***]",
  "ownership": "[HANG0] * The dreadful <i>Hulk</i> mag is history (<i>woohoo!</i>)\n[HANG0] * Spider-Man returns, hoping to salvage <i>something</i> from the early part of this year\n[HANG0] * Sub-Mariner takes on the FF yet again\n[HANG0] * and what <i>this</i>?&nbsp; \"Dr. Strange\" takes on Iron Man...<i>what?</i>"
}